&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our products and technologies require an extraordinary team. A team that will mold tomorrow’s technologies while deploying today’s best. We are an intrinsically motivated team that has a passion for solving problems and empowering each other every day to develop our skills, knowing that there is always room for growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our propulsion systems rely on tightly integrated avionics—including sensors, actuators, controllers, and instrumentation—to ensure precise operation and mission success. As an &lt;strong&gt;Avionics Technician&lt;/strong&gt;, you will collaborate with engineering and operations teams to build, assemble, and test avionics hardware for flight and test applications. Your work will directly support the reliability, safety, and readiness of engine electrical systems that are critical to defense and aerospace missions. Attention to detail, adherence to standards, and a commitment to quality are essential in this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, assemble, and test avionics hardware, including instrumentation, actuators, wire harnesses, sensors, and engine control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform troubleshooting, diagnosis, and root-cause analysis on electrical and electronic systems; recommend and implement corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute test procedures, document results, and maintain detailed build and inspection records in accordance with company and regulatory standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret and work from engineering drawings, wiring diagrams, and electrical schematics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform precision assembly of high-tolerance electro-mechanical components and sub-systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all builds comply with applicable aerospace and defense standards (e.g., J-STD-001, IPC-A-610, IPC/WHMA-A-620 and MIL-STD requirements).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with design engineers to provide feedback for manufacturability, assembly improvements, and design validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a safe, organized, and compliant work environment following ESD, FOD, and cleanroom protocols as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-school diploma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2+ years&lt;/strong&gt; of experience assembling and testing avionics or electronic hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;digital and analog circuits&lt;/strong&gt;, sensors, and control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in troubleshooting electrical systems, including use of oscilloscopes, multimeters, logic analyzers, and other diagnostic tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated hands-on proficiency with electrical builds, wire harnessing, and soldering to aerospace standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with &lt;strong&gt;high-precision and tight-tolerance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current or prior &lt;strong&gt;J-STD-001&lt;/strong&gt; certification (or equivalent).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with &lt;strong&gt;IC circuits&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;PCB design&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;electr

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ursa Major is&amp;nbsp;looking for&amp;nbsp;an experienced&amp;nbsp;Buyer&amp;nbsp;to join our team, who will report to the&amp;nbsp;Procurement&amp;nbsp;Lead.&amp;nbsp;You will&amp;nbsp;increase&amp;nbsp;operational&amp;nbsp;efficiency by&amp;nbsp;engaging with&amp;nbsp;our&amp;nbsp;suppliers, issuing purchase orders, coordinating deliveries, and communicating timelines to internal&amp;nbsp;customers.&amp;nbsp;We prefer that you are&amp;nbsp;proficient in informational flow and communication, which are&amp;nbsp;necessary to succeed&amp;nbsp;at a smaller, technical organization.&amp;nbsp;You will&amp;nbsp;support&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;Manufacturing&amp;nbsp;team&amp;nbsp;while&amp;nbsp;facilitating&amp;nbsp;engineering goals and supporting all organizational groups.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We prefer that you are&amp;nbsp;comfortable using modern ERP systems, MS Office suite,&amp;nbsp;project management software,&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;have&amp;nbsp;excellent communication skills.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage purchase orders for raw materials, additive and subtractive manufacturing components, services, and equipment needed for manufacturing.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively monitor and communicate with Supply Chain leadership and internal customers on the status of open purchase orders and delivery timelines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate favorable pricing, payment terms, and delivery schedules with new and existing suppliers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Support and help drive oversight of the supplier management system, ensuring compliance with company standards and regulations (ITAR/EAR, FAR/DFAR).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;strong relationships with suppliers to ensure prompt deliveries and&amp;nbsp;optimal&amp;nbsp;pricing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, analyze, and report on supplier performance metrics, delivery commitments, and corrective actions as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and support supplier non-disclosure agreement creation and processing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and ability to&amp;nbsp;manage multiple engine programs in a fast-paced environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve any issues related to price discrepancies, delayed shipments, or damaged goods.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement cost savings opportunities and alternative suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams such as&amp;nbsp;Engineering,&amp;nbsp;Material&amp;nbsp;Control,&amp;nbsp;Quality,&amp;nbsp;Finance,&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;meet project and production timelines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of experience in&amp;nbsp;procurement,&amp;nbsp;purchasing, or&amp;nbsp;supply chain, preferably in a manufacturing&amp;nbsp;environment&amp;nbsp;(aerospace experience is a plus).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency&amp;nbsp;in hardware-centered production environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management&am

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ursa Major is seeking a Chief Engineer, Vehicle to serve as the technical authority and architectural owner for the Draper Engine Vehicle program. This individual will be accountable for the end-to-end vehicle technical baseline, ensuring the successful integration of propulsion, structures, avionics, GNC, thermal, and mission systems into a flight-worthy, scalable vehicle solution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Chief Engineer, you will provide technical leadership across the full lifecycle—from requirements definition and trade studies through design, integration, test, and flight operations—while partnering closely with Program Management, Manufacturing, Mission Assurance, and Business Development. This role is critical to delivering reliable, high-performance systems to government and commercial customers on aggressive schedules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Authority &amp;amp; Architecture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and maintain the vehicle system architecture, technical baseline, and configuration for the Draper Engine Vehicle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the final technical decision authority for vehicle-level design trades, requirements allocation, and risk acceptance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure propulsion (Draper engine) is fully integrated into the vehicle system with appropriate margins, interfaces, and operational envelopes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Engineering &amp;amp; Integration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead vehicle-level systems engineering, including requirements flow-down, interface control, verification &amp;amp; validation (V&amp;amp;V), and configuration management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee cross-disciplinary integration across:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Propulsion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structures &amp;amp; airframe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GNC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Avionics &amp;amp; software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thermal &amp;amp; TPS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mission &amp;amp; flight systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chair technical reviews including SRR, PDR, CDR, TRR, and FRR.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Execution Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Program Management to balance performance, cost, schedule, and risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support proposal efforts, customer technical interchange meetings (TIMs), and design reviews with government and commercial customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify technical risks early and lead mitigation plans through test, analysis, or design iteration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Test, Qualification &amp;amp; Flight Readiness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and approve vehicle-level test strategies including ground testing, qualification, and flight test.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data-driven decisions using analysis, modeling, and test results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical sign-off for vehicle readiness and flight authorization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Mentorship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical leadership and ment

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ursa Major is seeking an experienced Corporate Development professional with previous experience in investment banking or corporate development who possesses a high level of critical thinking skills, a proactive work ethic, financial modeling expertise and excels in a fast-paced environment to join our growing Finance Team. The Corporate Development and Finance Senior Associate will support the Senior Director of Corporate Development as it pertains to M&amp;amp;A, fundraising, investor relations and corporate financial planning. These include, but are not limited to, financial modeling, due diligence activities, forecasting, analyzing other financial and operational metrics and communicating strategic rationale to executives for Ursa Major. The Corporate Development and Finance Senior Associate will collaborate with the corporate leadership team to produce reliable, accurate, comparable, and timely analysis that drives major transactions at the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transaction Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Execute financial modeling and valuation analysis for potential M&amp;amp;A opportunities, joint ventures, and fundraising rounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due Diligence:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a central point of contact during the diligence process, managing data rooms and coordinating across legal, tax, and product teams to identify risks and synergies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Draft high-impact presentations for the Board of Directors and Executive Leadership Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Investor Relations:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the preparation of materials for investor updates, earnings calls, and prospective funding pitches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Forecasting and Consolidation:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive the periodic consolidation of financials across various business lines to provide a unified view of company performance while tracking KPIs to provide insights into performance, helping leadership drive strategy decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of experience in Investment Banking, Management Consulting, Corporate Development, or a high-growth FP&amp;amp;A environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with a variety of deal structures, including M&amp;amp;A, carve-outs, equity investments, and joint ventures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong financial modeling and analytical skills, including experience building complex financial models from scratch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and oral communication skills with the ability to work cross-functionally and present to leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of ownership and curiosity; thrives in fast-moving, scrappy environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colorado law requires us to tell you the base compensation range of this role, which is $100,000 - $135,000, determined by your education, experience, knowledge, skills, and abilities. What we &lt;em&gt;can’t&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;quantify for you are the exciting challenges, supportive team, and amazing culture we enjoy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are bringing a new model to space access: one in which every link in an enormous value chain isn’t limited by those around it. We design rocket engines and propulsion solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our products and technologies require an extraordinary team. A team that will ensure the security of tomorrow’s technologies while deploying today’s best. We are an intrinsically motivated team with a passion for solving problems and empowering each other every day to develop our skills, knowing that there is always room for growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cybersecurity Administrator II is a technical leadership role responsible for overseeing the organization’s cybersecurity strategy with a primary focus on risk mitigation for Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI). This position involves managing advanced security infrastructure, conducting high-level risk assessments, and leading the implementation of security policies to ensure compliance with federal regulations such as NIST SP 800-171 and CMMC. The Administrator will collaborate with stakeholders to reduce the probability of a material impact due to a cyber event, specifically targeting the protection of sensitive data flows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk Mitigation &amp;amp; CUI Oversight&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify and Prioritize Risks:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct high-level risk assessments and threat modeling specifically focused on the protection of CUI and Federal Contract Information (FCI).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop Mitigation Strategies:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee the implementation and advancement of comprehensive risk mitigation strategies to ensure data integrity and confidentiality at the CUI level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Flow Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Work with stakeholders and external vendors to ensure risk management and CUI handling protocols are embedded in all applicable organizational processes and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Controls:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish and enforce advanced security policies and protocols across the organization to meet stringent federal data protection standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security &amp;amp; Compliance Management&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure Optimization:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage and optimize security infrastructure, including firewalls, IDS/IPS, and SIEM systems, ensuring they are tuned to detect threats against sensitive data environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Federal Compliance Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the technical implementation of compliance programs to adhere to CMMC, NIST (800-171/800-53), FISMA, and FedRAMP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; Auditing:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and maintain critical documentation, including System Security Plans (SSPs), Risk Assessment Reports (RARs), and Plan of Action and Milestones (POA&amp;amp;M) specifically for CUI-governed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit Readiness:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee regular compliance audits and assessments, ensuring all findings related to CUI protection are addressed promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;stro

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As Ursa Major expands into the realm of solid propulsion, we’re assembling an innovative and nimble team in order to bring needed improvements to the SRM industry.&amp;nbsp; Applying the latest technologies to an outdated business model, we are able toimprove cost, lead time, and flexibility without impacting reliability.&amp;nbsp; Ursa Major prioritizes engineering excellence, building in-house capabilities in energetics, ballistics, and composites with an emphasis on novel designs focused on manufacturability and high-rate scalability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Development engineers are primarily responsible for all aspects of the design, fabrication and test of development prototype hardware for Ursa Major’s solid motor program as well as process development for new and novel approaches to manufacturing. &amp;nbsp;Success on this team requires an understanding of solid rocket propulsion fundamentals, mechanical and fluid systems, strong critical thinking skills, attention to detail, organization, and effective communication across discipline groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean sheet design of novel solid rocket motor elements with limited guidance from subject matter experts, including relevant analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional communications to ensure designs satisfy the needs of each stakeholder.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain proper documentation of all designs including design reviews, drawings, test plans, requirements verification, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate novel manufacturing approaches and support experimentation to validate conceptual approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with procurement team to identify potential supply chain risks and mitigate appropriately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate new materials for SRM design solutions, including material properties, manufacturability, and supply chain availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design, fabrication and assembly of prototype hardware and tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide dispositions for discrepant hardware including supporting analysis if required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop test plans including required instrumentation and coordinate with test team to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review test data to ensure the product is operating as expected and support design changes as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own failure investigations as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain aggressive but achievable product schedules that proactively identify and mitigate high-risk design decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate CAD models and drawings that are consistent with internal best practices and ASME Y14.5-2009 using Siemens NX software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Aerospace Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or other applicable discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of professional rocket propulsion experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of solid rocket motor fundamentals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Programming competency in any language&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position requires that the employee be eligible and maintain eligibility for a Secret Clearance.&lt;/strong

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The future of aerospace and defense starts here.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ursa Major was founded to revolutionize how America and its allies access and apply high-performance propulsion, from hypersonics to solid rocket motors, satellite maneuvering and launch. We design and deliver propulsion and defense systems that solve the most urgent and critical national security demands.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As Ursa Major expands into the realm of solid propulsion, we’re assembling the most innovative and nimble team to unseat the reigning players. We’re applying the latest technologies to an outdated business model that improves cost, lead time, and flexibility without impacting reliability. We must continue to build in-house capabilities in energetics, ballistics, and composites with an emphasis on novel designs focused on manufacturability and high-rate scalability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role requires a safety-first approach, a willingness and desire to learn and an attention to detail mindset. As a part of the development technician team, you will be a key component of the energetics manufacturing process. You will be responsible for the production and transportation/storage of energetic materials.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a development technician, you will be responsible for identifying process improvements and solving problems as they appear. Ability to provide engineers and other operations team members with valuable feedback will allow for quick scalability and growth&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roles and Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full scale propellant mixing – Prepares materials and performs full-scale mixing for all production and development programs, confirming acceptable weights prior to releasing the materials to mixing and casting operations. The technician will also perform full-scale mixes for new programs/new formulations as they are introduced to the site. The technician is responsible for requisitioning and organizing the materials and processing required for the mix, as well as cleaning and maintaining full scale mix equipment. Technician will perform these duties under the general direction of engineer and the team supervisor, using established, well-defined methods and calculations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Milling – The technician will assemble mills and mill materials for full-scale propellant mixes and weigh material bins to correct weight for propellant mixing. Technician is responsible for disassembly, cleaning, and re-assembly of full-scale milling equipment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned - Such as but not limited to: AP prep for milling, final assembly of prototype energetic articles, development sample preparation, and support of new production initiatives and schedules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining a clean and organized space that passes FOD critical standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to follow and develop a preventative maintenance schedule with the assistance of engineering or chief technician.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing and available to work other shifts or overtime as needed to meet production schedules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work from elevated platforms, ascend ladders, and transport 35 lbs. repetitively.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medically cleared to wear a respirator and operate powered industrial vehicle (and obtain company issued license as appropriate).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
