&lt;li&gt;Ensure Test-Like-You-Fly practices during ground operations at our Berthoud campus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Author and execute procedures for checkouts, propellant load, and hotfire operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the ground and flight operations of Ursa Major’s missions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in data review, failure investigations, and sequence preparation for static fire testing and flight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with test ranges and external agencies to plan and execute flight test campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead customer status updates and milestone reviews for both programmatic and technical content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present and provide technical review in customer meetings and integration reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a subject matter expert on Ursa Major’s hypersonic vehicle and propulsion systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel to customer sites to lead product integration, support checkouts, and assist in test and flight campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct system data review to support fast-paced customer test campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot system and component hardware issues in the field, develop solutions with the Ursa team and customer, and lead implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement product improvements focused on customer needs, risk reduction, and end-use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B.S. in Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for developing customer relationships and ensuring mission success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail, curiosity, and relentless in resolving problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with aerospace hardware&lt;/li&gt;
